{"key":"processedPost-6844382","value":{"id":6844382,"first":6730011,"last":6844384,"when":1177767098,"utime":"04/28/07 04:31 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I was planning on spawning to straw with a pure vermiculite casing, would that require a casing layer?</blockquote><br />If you put a vermiculite casing on, that IS a casing layer, however, don't screw up your straw by dumping verm on it. Straw fruits best uncased.<br />Never add a casing layer after pinning starts.  It leads to contamination under the casing layer, and also causes the pins that have formed to abort in many cases.<br />RR"}}